An '''event movie''' is a [[film]] whose release itself is considered a major event, such as an anticipated sequel or a big budget film with major stars generating considerable attention and state-of-the-art special effects.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://miown.com/websites/mmi/mmiglossary.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-06-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714100857/http://miown.com/websites/mmi/mmiglossary.html |archivedate=2011-07-14 |df= }}</ref> An event movie is usually the highest-grossing box office movie in the particular year and becomes a part of popular culture. [[Steven Spielberg]]'s 1975 movie ''[[Jaws (film)|Jaws]]'' is considered the first event movie.<ref>[https://movies.yahoo.com/feature/movie-talk-jaws-turns-35.html 'Jaws,' The First 'Event Movie,' Turns 35]</ref>

