{{Orphan|date=January 2017}}
The "Nines Club" describes people who have achieved [[third class honours]] results in each of their three years of a standard length [[Bachelor's degree]] whilst at [[University]].   Bachelor's degree candidates who achieve a result not within the 3rd class bracket (normally 40 to 50%) in any of their three years do not qualify for the "Nines Club".

The term is normally reserved for Bachelor's degree candidates who attended [[University of Oxford|Oxford]] or [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge]] Universities.

[[Carol Vorderman]], having studied [[Engineering]] at [[Sidney Sussex College, Cambridge]] and co-presented [[Countdown (game show)|Countdown]] alongside [[Richard Whiteley]], is a noted member of the "Nines Club".

