{{Infobox language |name=Su' |nativename= |states=[[Laos]] |speakers={{sigfig|2360|2}} |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Bahnaric languages|Bahnaric]] |fam3=[[West Bahnaric languages|West]] |fam4=[[Laven language|Laven]] |iso3=sqq |glotto=souu1238 |glottorefname=Sou }}
'''Su' ''' (autonym: {{ipa|ɟruʔ}}) is a [[Mon–Khmer languages|Mon–Khmer language]] of the [[Bahnaric languages|Bahnaric]] branch spoken in [[Attapeu Province]], [[Laos]]. The 1995 [[Attapeu Province|Attapeu]] census recorded a population of only 124 speakers in [[Sanamxay District|Sanamsay District]]. Su' autonyms are identical with that of the Jru' (known to the Lao as "Laven"), but they consider themselves to be a separate ethnic group (Sidwell 2003:19). There could also possibly be speakers in [[Stung Treng Province]], [[Cambodia]].
Su' speakers live in villages on both sides of Route 18, from Ban Chanto to about 10&nbsp;km before Ban Mai.
==References== {{reflist}} *Sidwell, Paul (2003). ''A Handbook of comparative Bahnaric, Vol. 1: West Bahnaric''. Pacific Linguistics, 551. Canberra: Research School of Pacific and Asian Studies, Australian National University.
