{{Expand Swahili|Wikipedia ya Kiswahili|date=August 2011}} {{Infobox website | name = {{Wiki favicon}} Swahili Wikipedia | screenshot = | logo = Wikipedia-logo-v2-sw.svg | logo_size = 140px | caption = | url = [http://sw.wikipedia.org/ sw.wikipedia.org] | commercial = No | location = [[Miami, Florida]] | type = [[Internet encyclopedia project]] | language = [[Swahili language|Swahili]] | registration = Optional | owner = [[Wikimedia Foundation]] | author = }}
The '''Swahili Wikipedia''' ({{lang-sw|{{#property:P1448}}}}) is the [[Swahili language]] edition of [[Wikipedia]]. It is currently one (and the first) of four language editions of Wikipedia in [[Niger–Congo languages]] with over 1,000 articles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/List_of_Wikipedias_by_language_group|title=List of Wikipedias by language group|work=wikimedia.org}}</ref> It is the largest language edition of Wikipedia in a Niger–Congo or Nilo-Saharan language, followed by the [[Yoruba Wikipedia]].
It was mentioned on August 27, 2006 in ''[[International Herald Tribune]]'' and ''[[New York Newsday]]'' articles on the struggles of smaller Wikipedia language editions.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2006/08/27/technology/27iht-wiki.2604689.html ''Building Wikipedia in African languages''], by Noam Cohen, [[International Herald Tribune]], August 27, 2006.</ref> In 2009, [[Google]] sponsored the creation of articles in the Swahili Wikipedia.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.nytimes.com/2010/01/25/technology/25link.html?_r=0|title = Hungry for New Content, Google Tries to Grow Its Own in Africa|date = January 24, 2010|accessdate = October 14, 2014|website = nytimes.com |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> On June 20, 2009, the Swahili Wikipedia gave its main page a makeover. As of {{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}, it has about {{formatnum:{{#expr:{{NUMBEROF|ARTICLES|sw}} round -3}}}} [[encyclopedia article|articles]], making it the 90th-largest Wikipedia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/List_of_Wikipedias|title=List of Wikipedias|work=wikimedia.org}}</ref>
