==Writing systems==
Vlax Romani is written using the [[Romani orthography]], which is a [[Latin script|Latin alphabet]] with several additional characters. In the area of the former [[Soviet Union]] it is also written in [[Cyrillic script|Cyrillic]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ilholocaustmuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/TheJournies.pdf |title=Journey of Besieged Languages|website=ilholocaustmuseum.org}}</ref>
